          Torque follows <strong class="text-frost-300">τ = m × B</strong> where
          <strong class="text-frost-300">m = N·I·A</strong>.
          H-bridge MOSFETs flip 11.1 V across each coil; closed-loop PWM with current sensing
          compensates for resistance drift as wire heats in vacuum.
          An Extended Kalman Filter on ESP32 CPU1 fuses IMU, magnetometer,
          and coarse sun sensors continuously.
